      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "A similar problem can be asked for infinite Sidon sets."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "8218daf136ef1047a57cf006cb4a5706541eb23c7acbf63761cdc04222d9e614",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Let $A$ be a finite Sidon set and $A+A=\\{s_1<\\cdots<s_t\\}$. Is it true that\\[\\frac{1}{t}\\sum_{1\\leq i<t}(s_{i+1}-s_i)^2 \\to \\infty\\]as $\\lvert A\\rvert\\to \\infty$?"
    }
  },
